1343
01:37:08.997 --> 01:37:12.601
I was the one who proposed.

1344
01:37:15.604 --> 01:37:18.641
Well, don't look
so panicky, George.


1345
01:37:18.674 --> 01:37:22.378
I was only
three-quarters serious.


1346
01:37:26.749 --> 01:37:30.486
Well, when you're completely
serious, ask me again.


1347
01:37:30.519 --> 01:37:34.623
I bet you say that
to all the girls.


1348
01:37:34.657 --> 01:37:36.559
No.

1349
01:37:41.697 --> 01:37:45.634
Thank you.
You hungry?


1350
01:37:45.668 --> 01:37:48.937
Yes.
Well, you're in luck.


1351
01:37:48.971 --> 01:37:53.642
Because today, your lunch is
being catered by the chicest,


1352
01:37:53.676 --> 01:37:57.580
most expensive French delicatessen
in all of San Francisco.


1353
01:37:57.613 --> 01:38:01.517
How did we swing that?
The owner's got a thing for ya.


1354
01:38:01.550 --> 01:38:04.353
It's out in the trunk of my car.
Can I help?


1355
01:38:04.387 --> 01:38:07.590
Why, you could set the table
and turn on some nice music...


1356
01:38:07.623 --> 01:38:09.658
and when I come back,
make me laugh, huh?


1357
01:38:09.692 --> 01:38:12.461
I'll try.
Don't worry.


1358
01:38:12.495 --> 01:38:16.331
If you can't make me
laugh, just hold my hand.


1359
01:38:38.086 --> 01:38:40.889
Hello?

1360
01:38:40.923 --> 01:38:44.660
Uh, no, she's not here
right now. Who's this?


1361
01:38:47.162 --> 01:38:50.132
Harry? Um...

1362
01:38:50.165 --> 01:38:55.037
Uh, would you... would you just
hold on for a minute, please?


1363
01:39:08.984 --> 01:39:10.986
Hello?

1364
01:39:12.688 --> 01:39:16.892
Harry, we're two mature adult human
beings, and I've decided to be honest.


1365
01:39:18.994 --> 01:39:22.931
No. Doris is not here right now,
but I'd like to talk to you.


1366
01:39:24.833 --> 01:39:26.502
Because I know
that you and Doris


1367
01:39:26.527 --> 01:39:29.128
are having a pretty rough
time right now, and...


1368
01:39:31.574 --> 01:39:35.010
Uh, we're very close friends.

1369
01:39:35.043 --> 01:39:39.014
I've known Doris for 20 years,
and I feel that through her, I know you.


1370
01:39:42.718 --> 01:39:46.188
We've been meeting this
same weekend for 20 years.


1371
01:39:50.192 --> 01:39:54.096
The retreat?
Uh, yeah.


1372
01:39:54.129 --> 01:39:58.233
I'll, uh... I'll get to
that in a minute, but, um,


1373
01:39:58.266 --> 01:40:01.637
first I'd like to tell you
something, Harry.


1374
01:40:01.670 --> 01:40:04.507
She loves you.

1375
01:40:04.540 --> 01:40:09.812
Well, I just know. Look. Maybe if I told
you a story she told me this morning,


1376
01:40:09.845 --> 01:40:12.581
maybe it would help you
understand.


1377
01:40:12.615 --> 01:40:17.953
Uh, a few months ago,
Doris was supposed to act as den mother...


1378
01:40:17.986 --> 01:40:22.224
for your 10-year-old daughter
and her Indian Guide group.


1379
01:40:22.257 --> 01:40:26.762
And Doris was a little late.
She was hung up at the store,


1380
01:40:26.795 --> 01:40:29.131
and she got home
about two hours late.


1381
01:40:29.164 --> 01:40:30.958
When she walked into the house,

1382
01:40:30.983 --> 01:40:34.603
she looked in the living room,
and you know what she saw?


1383
01:40:34.637 --> 01:40:38.841
A rather overweight, balding, middle-aged
man with a feather on his head...


1384
01:40:38.874 --> 01:40:43.011
sitting cross-legged on the
